Source: depthcharge-tools
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Alper Nebi Yasak <alpernebiyasak@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 12)
Standards-Version: 4.4.0
Vcs-Browser: https://salsa.debian.org/alpernebbi-guest/depthcharge-support
Vcs-Git: https://salsa.debian.org/alpernebbi-guest/depthcharge-support.git

Package: depthcharge-tools
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, u-boot-tools, vboot-kernel-utils, cgpt, linux-base
Description: Tools for ChromeOS firmware/bootloader integration
 The built-in firmware on ChromeOS devices has a custom verified boot
 implementation that can only boot from special images written to
 partitions of a certain type. This package provides tools that create
 these images for the running system and manage these partitions.

Package: depthcharge-support
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, depthcharge-tools
Description: ChromeOS firmware/bootloader integration
 This package keeps ChromeOS devices bootable via the firmware's custom
 verified boot method by automatically building boot images and writing
 them to appropriate partitions whenever a kernel or an initramfs change
 happens.
